"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function get_active_figure() returns the current active figure using plt.gcf(), but it is called after plt.close() has been executed, which closes the figure. Therefore, when get_active_figure() is called, it will return None, and the subsequent code that tries to add text to the axis will fail because ax is associated with a closed figure.\", \"patch\": \"11c11\\n< plt.close()\\n---\\n> plt.show()\"}"